cs.FL, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with infinite words and their properties, which are central topics in formal languages and automata theory.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves combinatorial and discrete structures such as palindromes and factors of words.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility as the paper may involve the study of entropy and compression of infinite words.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper may involve algorithms for computing the least number of palindromic factors in an infinite word.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper may involve the study of the computational complexity of determining the least number of palindromic factors in an infinite word.
